reviews.review: They did the best they could with what Rian Johnson gave them to work with. Very fast paced and super dense but overall pretty happy with the outcome. Just the right amount of creativity and callbacks. Good work JJ, cast, everyone. Sorry you had to waste time undoing everything The Last Jedi did.
one of the best Star Wars movie from the new trilogy and that's how you ended Star Wars series
Unimaginative, lazy, and inconsistent. Plot is all over the place.
Loved it. Hit on the questions that everyone had and was a fun ride.
I really enjoyed the movie with my son in 3D.
It was Star Wars, always awesome. Not really sure I liked the ending though, saw what was coming a mile away. However, I love the characters, the story, the world building.

Plot holes, retcons, and blasphemy galore. This film ruins the ending of Anakin's arc in the first six films. Rey is now only almost a Mary Sue. In firm honesty, it feels like this film is in a wrestling match with TLJ. A good movie in a vacuum, but adding the context of the other films drops the rating further. Fan service that felt at times like fan fiction(bad), and fan service that felt like love notes from George Lucas himself (good). Yet still not the fan service everyone wanted: Obi-Wan force ghost, Anakin Force Ghost, etc. 

The Knights of Ren were the biggest disappointment in the film, after their revels in EP7 and lack of showing in EP8 they were finally shown in the film. Only to be revealed to be a bunch of cannon fodder. This leads to probably the greatest critique of the film, this should have been at least a three hour film. Two hours and twenty minutes was not enough, thus story arcs feel jerky at times in pacing.

A pathetic attempt to close off the Skywalker saga practically undoing everything that the original Lucas films established and negating an actually well developed story. There are a multitude of plot holes that either are never explained or explained so poorly JJ has no choice but to wipe to a different scene every 10 seconds at breakneck pace. The only solace I could find in the film was the acting by Adam Driver, Oscar Isaac, Daisy Ridley, and John Boyega, as well as the score, but even that one was derivative and at times beyond cheesy. Palpatine was a joke. The movie spent half of its time undoing the last one. 1/5 would not recommend. Attack of the Clones was better.

I really enjoyed the movie.  It answered some major questions (Rey’s lineage, Kylo’s struggle).  It was an impossible movie to make and JJ Abrams did a great job!  Witty humor, exciting, sad, epic ending!

Absolutely terrible storytelling, pacing, acting, dialogue, etc. This seems to be a movie written by a group of high school students saying "you know what would be cool? lets do that!" with no thought on the story arc or character motivations. Its a shame that I've been alive to witness two awful Star Wars trilogies.
